\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Advanced robotics is changing the landscape of manufacturing, healthcare, and daily life. Robots with enhanced dexterity, artificial intelligence, and autonomous decision-making capabilities are increasingly taking on complex tasks, from performing surgeries to assisting in disaster recovery. The development of soft robotics, which mimics the flexibility and adaptability of biological organisms, is opening up new possibilities for robots in delicate and dynamic environments. As robots become more integrated into society, ethical considerations, including job displacement and human-robot interaction, are gaining importance.}